      "type": "prompt",
      "title": "Prompt",
      "description": "Infer one parameter value from product evidence.",
      "position": {
        "x": 930,
        "y": 240
      },
      "inputs": [
        "bundle",
        "images"
      ],
      "outputs": [
        "prompt",
        "images"
      ],
      "config": {
        "prompt": {
          "template": "You infer exactly one product parameter value from product evidence.\\nUse the current product title, description, images, and target parameter metadata.\\n\\nProduct title: \"{{bundle.sourceTitle}}\"\\nProduct description: \"{{bundle.sourceDescription}}\"\\nCurrent value: \"{{bundle.currentValue}}\"\\nTarget parameter JSON: {{bundle.targetParameter}}\\nFull parsed bundle JSON: {{bundle}}\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON with this exact schema:\\n{\"parameterId\":\"\",\"value\":\"\",\"confidence\":0}\\n\\nRules:\\n1. Set parameterId to targetParameter.id.\\n2. Infer only the requested target parameter, not any other product attribute.\\n3. If targetParameter.optionLabels is not empty and selectorType is select, dropdown, radio, checklist, or checkbox, use only labels from optionLabels.\\n4. For select, dropdown, and radio, return one label only.\\n5. For checklist, return a comma-separated list of supported labels only.\\n6. For checkbox, return the configured option label when true or an empty string when false/unsupported.\\n7. For text and textarea, return a concise value supported by the title, description, or images.\\n8. For target parameters named like Model name, Model, or Nazwa modelu, infer the product/model/design name from the title; when the title uses pipe separators, this is usually the first segment before the first |.\\n9. Do not return an empty value for text or textarea when the title, description, or images provide any usable evidence.\\n10. Return an empty value only when there is genuinely no product evidence for the requested parameter, and set confidence to 0.\\n11. Do not invent dimensions, material, color, theme, compatibility, or brand facts not supported by evidence.\\n12. JSON only. No markdown, no code fences, no commentary."
        }
      },
